01:55.000 --> 01:58.527
Dearly beloved, we are
gathered here in the sight of God...

01:58.760 --> 02:01.889
...and in the face of this family
to join together this...

02:34.720 --> 02:38.520
What do you feel like, Italian, Thai?

02:38.760 --> 02:42.651
- Are we really gonna do this?
- Do what? I'm hungry.

02:42.840 --> 02:46.367
- Not talk about it.
- I'll probably get turned down.

02:47.120 --> 02:49.964
The trial... Nobody gets in this thing.
It's false hope.

02:50.160 --> 02:52.891
Did you hear what the doctor said?
Were you even listening?

02:53.080 --> 02:56.289
- I mean, he said the prognosis is...
- He said he couldn't predict.

02:56.480 --> 02:58.721
No, he said that the trial
was your best shot.

02:58.920 --> 03:01.890
You don't want to do it, fine.
Do it for me. I can live with that.

03:02.080 --> 03:05.163
- I just want to think about it.
- There's nothing to think about.

03:06.520 --> 03:10.161
I don't care if you get fat.
I don't care if you lose your hair.

03:10.360 --> 03:13.330
You're applying for this trial.
You're gonna be accepted.

03:13.520 --> 03:18.162
Do you understand me?
I am not losing you.

03:19.640 --> 03:23.531
As soon as I get to the office,
I'll make the call.

03:35.760 --> 03:40.926
DMV? Really?
I've never even seen you drive.

03:41.120 --> 03:45.444
That little fella, the one through
the glass, his name is Glen Carter.

03:45.640 --> 03:48.405
His mother calls him Jelly Bean.

03:48.600 --> 03:50.762
A loathsome individual
who, sad to say...

03:51.160 --> 03:54.004
...possesses an uncanny ability
to locate anything.

04:03.200 --> 04:05.851
I presume you've heard
of Justin Kenyon?

04:06.040 --> 04:09.681
The smiling public face of
The Militia Movement. Who hasn't?

04:09.880 --> 04:15.250
Yes. The very voice of reason,
the rebel darling of the fringe right...

04:15.480 --> 04:19.166
...charming, rustic, camera-ready,
the perfect spokesman...

04:19.399 --> 04:23.200
...to spin vile hatred and prejudice
into treacly dross...

04:23.400 --> 04:25.402
...that passes for plainspoken
common sense.

04:25.600 --> 04:28.444
- Forget it.
- Excuse me?

04:28.640 --> 04:31.928
Justice knows exactly who
Justin Kenyon is. We know what he is.

04:32.160 --> 04:36.802
The Church of the Shield is a cesspool
of polygamy, doomsday paranoia...

04:37.040 --> 04:39.202
...ritualized elder and child abuse...

04:39.400 --> 04:42.449
...but he also has four of the most
prominent civil rights attorneys...

04:42.640 --> 04:44.961
...in the country on retainer.
We can't touch him.

04:45.160 --> 04:47.322
How do you suppose he pays
for those lawyers?

04:47.520 --> 04:50.046
- Charitable contributions?
- His church has been audited...

04:50.240 --> 04:54.802
...by the IRS every year for the past
decade. His books are impeccable.

04:56.040 --> 04:57.485
So are mine.

04:59.040 --> 05:02.010
Justin Kenyon,
head of The Church of the Shield...

05:02.200 --> 05:06.842
...a polygamist cult located
on a 15,000-acre reserve...

05:07.040 --> 05:08.451
...in the Smoky Mountains.

05:08.640 --> 05:11.644
Kenyon declared it a nation-state
and petitioned to secede in court...

05:11.840 --> 05:14.002
- ...three decades ago.
- According to Reddington...

05:14.200 --> 05:17.010
...Kenyon has dozens of shipping
containers buried on his property.

05:17.200 --> 05:19.885
Terrorists, cartels and criminals
contract with him...

05:20.080 --> 05:21.923
...to store cargo, no questions asked.

05:22.120 --> 05:25.408
Reddington compiled a partial inventory
from his sources.

05:25.600 --> 05:29.207
It includes all manner of contraband,
from drugs and hot merchandise...

05:29.400 --> 05:33.530
...to military ordnance, antiaircraft guns,
missiles, RPGs, Semtex.

05:33.720 --> 05:36.849
Sounds like a one-stop storage facility
for the criminal underworld.

05:37.040 --> 05:41.523
In 1982, Kenyon published a book
entitled The Silver Bear Prophecies...

05:41.720 --> 05:45.930
...which he purported were delivered to him
by the spirit of an ancient druid elder.

05:46.120 --> 05:48.805
In it, he claims to be
the latter-day incarnation...

05:49.000 --> 05:52.288
...of an entity the Silver Bear
called "the Ken'yon."

05:52.480 --> 05:55.324
- How convenient.
- Ken'yon and his followers...

05:55.520 --> 05:59.764
...will ascend into heaven for six days
and return to, and I quote:

06:00.000 --> 06:04.847
"Rain fire upon the new Babylon,
the defiled States of America...

06:05.040 --> 06:07.520
...and our children shall cleanse
her streets...

06:07.760 --> 06:09.762
...with the blood
of her founder's enemies."

06:09.960 --> 06:13.009
According to Reddington,
Kenyon has fallen off the radar.

06:13.200 --> 06:15.089
His clients have been unable
to reach him...

06:15.280 --> 06:17.567
...or anyone on the compound
since last Saturday.

06:17.760 --> 06:20.491
Which means they don't have access
to their stored goods.

06:20.680 --> 06:24.082
As you can imagine, this makes
a number of very dangerous people...

06:24.320 --> 06:25.765
...very, very nervous.

06:28.400 --> 06:30.209
Not interested. Can't be done.

06:30.400 --> 06:32.846
Glen, you have found things for me
with far less to go on.

06:33.080 --> 06:35.811
Ernie's retirement party's tonight.
I got to pick up the shrimp.

06:36.040 --> 06:39.169
You found Jerry Minkie's wife
after she ran off with the Uber driver...

06:39.360 --> 06:41.761
...the one with the Subaru.
- I don't even like shrimp.

06:42.000 --> 06:43.923
You found the, uh, other guy,
who was that?

06:44.120 --> 06:47.203
That mobster who was hiding out
in Needles.

06:47.400 --> 06:50.131
Glen, look, you and l...

06:50.320 --> 06:54.370
We've had our differences but I have
enormous respect for your abilities.

06:54.600 --> 06:57.126
You know that.
If anyone can help me, it's you.

06:57.320 --> 07:01.928
It's not the shrimp. It's the dip,
that sauce. I don't like sauces.

07:03.560 --> 07:05.050
Forget it. I don't need this.

07:05.240 --> 07:08.608
- What are you so upset about?
- There isn't a retirement party, is there?

07:08.800 --> 07:10.962
You're making it up.
That's what this is about.

07:11.200 --> 07:14.329
This is what you want,
to see me get all lathered up.

07:14.520 --> 07:16.807
You're pathological.
You realize that, right?

07:17.040 --> 07:19.771
Ernie's shrimp platter?
You can't be serious.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.082
Do you even see the irony in that?

07:26.640 --> 07:30.326
- Tell me about the safe.
- Glen, I'm upset.

07:30.520 --> 07:33.410
Your spook friend,
he said it was critical.

07:43.400 --> 07:47.246
As I've already told you, he said
there is a safe in St. Petersburg...

07:47.480 --> 07:51.565
...on the second floor of I don't know
where, a bank, an apartment.

07:51.760 --> 07:53.683
He died before he could tell me more.

07:53.880 --> 07:57.248
The spook, what was his name?

07:58.240 --> 08:02.040
- Alan Fitch.
- Alan...

08:03.480 --> 08:06.211
- Fitch!
- Fitch!

08:08.600 --> 08:10.807
Kenyon's been off the grid
for three days.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.241
According to his own words,
that gives us 72 hours...

08:13.440 --> 08:15.488
...before he delivers his version
of Armageddon.

08:15.720 --> 08:17.722
His counsel has assured us
nothing is amiss...

08:17.920 --> 08:21.242
...and under no circumstances
are we to attempt direct contact.

08:21.440 --> 08:24.649
They already won two civil judgments
on Kenyon's behalf for harassment.

08:24.840 --> 08:26.444
He's sitting on enough ordnance...

08:26.640 --> 08:29.086
...to arm a third-world country.
- This could go south...

08:29.320 --> 08:31.766
...and end up looking very badly.
- I don't give a damn.

08:31.960 --> 08:35.520
Well, that's a luxury we cannot afford,
not after Waco and Ruby Ridge.

08:35.720 --> 08:40.282
We're looking at a tactical nightmare,
78 square miles of virgin forest...

08:40.480 --> 08:43.370
...a mountain stronghold
with enough food and potable water...

08:43.559 --> 08:45.801
...to withstand an armed siege
for months.

08:46.040 --> 08:48.725
And even if by some miracle
we manage to put down resistance...

08:48.960 --> 08:51.201
...and seize that compound
without loss of life...

08:51.400 --> 08:54.961
...without harm coming to
the 26 children who reside there...

08:55.160 --> 08:56.650
...what if Reddington is wrong?

08:56.840 --> 08:58.763
Lizzy, exactly when have I been wrong?

08:58.960 --> 09:01.361
I told you,
there are political considerations.

09:01.600 --> 09:04.080
If we raid Kenyon's compound
and come up empty-handed...

09:04.280 --> 09:06.521
- You will not come up empty-handed.
- But if we do...

09:06.720 --> 09:08.927
...then we'll have validated
Kenyon's allegations...

09:09.120 --> 09:11.487
...that the government
are a pack of jackbooted thugs.

09:11.680 --> 09:14.126
We'll have raised him up
as a martyr for the Constitution.

09:14.360 --> 09:15.850
That's exactly what he wants.

09:16.040 --> 09:17.804
I have gone to considerable lengths...

09:18.000 --> 09:20.401
...to point you and your team
in the right direction...

09:20.600 --> 09:25.606
...and now, due to political
considerations, people will die.

09:25.800 --> 09:28.565
And when they do
and the bureaucrats decide...

09:28.760 --> 09:31.889
...that the loss of innocent lives
trumps their career prospects...

09:32.080 --> 09:34.162
...you be sure to give me a call.

09:42.560 --> 09:46.406
Unit B61 to Dispatch, run a check
on a late-model Chevy van...

09:46.640 --> 09:51.487
...Tennessee plate number
Delta-Oscar-Charlie-7-7-1.

09:53.000 --> 09:56.721
Unit
B261, that tag number is 10-40 stolen...

09:56.920 --> 10:00.049
...registered to a 2005 Jeep Cherokee.
Copy?

10:00.280 --> 10:01.964
Copy that.

10:04.280 --> 10:06.328
Show us your hands!

10:08.960 --> 10:11.247
Hands outside the window now!

10:15.560 --> 10:16.607
What the...

10:17.240 --> 10:20.130
Hold your fire! It's just a...

10:27.120 --> 10:29.885
ATF estimates there was
enough Semtex in that van...

10:30.080 --> 10:31.411
...to level five blocks.

10:31.600 --> 10:33.400
- Anything on the victims?
- Vaporized.

10:33.560 --> 10:35.722
The presumed dead include
two Alabama state troopers...

10:35.920 --> 10:36.967
...and the occupant of the van.

10:38.440 --> 10:39.487
Yeah?

10:39.680 --> 10:41.603
We just got footage of the explosion.

10:41.800 --> 10:44.201
Hold your fire! It's just a...

10:45.400 --> 10:46.606
It's just a what?

10:46.800 --> 10:48.600
VIN numbers on the van's differential...

10:48.720 --> 10:51.007
...match a vehicle
registered to Kenyon's church.

10:51.200 --> 10:53.328
Judge is signing a search warrant
as we speak.

10:53.520 --> 10:56.444
Also, the plates were swapped out
for one stolen off a Cherokee...

10:56.640 --> 10:59.246
...at a truck stop five miles
from the Kenyon compound.

10:59.440 --> 11:02.922
I got a hit on another set of plates
stolen from the same location.

11:03.120 --> 11:06.681
Another van passed through a tollbooth
on the MD 200 headed into D.C.

11:06.880 --> 11:08.840
Reddington was right. If we'd listened...

11:08.880 --> 11:12.521
...we wouldn't have fanatics joyriding
with enough ordnance to level a small city.

11:12.720 --> 11:14.370
Ressler and Keen,
get to that compound.

11:14.560 --> 11:16.210
Warrant should be
sealed and delivered.

11:16.440 --> 11:19.171
Navabi, the van.
Find out everything you can.

11:22.480 --> 11:24.244
Harold Cooper.

11:25.120 --> 11:27.407
Dr. Levin, hello.

11:29.360 --> 11:31.408
Was I accepted?

11:35.000 --> 11:36.604
I see.

11:37.600 --> 11:40.251
You know, Jeff,
you don't owe me an apology.

11:40.440 --> 11:45.731
I know you did everything you could.
Thank you.

11:56.720 --> 11:59.849
Hey, I just got off the phone
with the doctor.

12:00.040 --> 12:02.850
I'm afraid it's bad news.

12:03.040 --> 12:05.691
I am not taking you to St. Petersburg.

12:05.880 --> 12:07.484
You are if you want to know
where the safe is.

12:07.680 --> 12:10.081
- How do I even know you've found it?
- You don't.

12:10.280 --> 12:14.080
But I got two weeks of vacation I got to take
before the end of the year or I lose it.

12:14.280 --> 12:16.362
- It's February.
- We could take your jet...

12:16.560 --> 12:20.406
...have a few laughs on the way, some
of those nuts, the honey-roasted ones.

12:20.600 --> 12:26.130
I want what I paid for,
the location of the safe.

12:26.320 --> 12:29.051
- Can I be honest with you?
- I doubt it.

12:30.600 --> 12:33.444
I've never been out of the country.

12:34.280 --> 12:40.811
My dad, our vacations as a kid, we drove
everywhere, South Dakota, Florida.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.970
But you, I look at you...

12:44.200 --> 12:47.443
...and all the places you go...

12:49.640 --> 12:54.248
...and I'd just like to do that once.

12:55.760 --> 12:58.525
Plus, I think it'd be fun.

12:58.720 --> 13:01.883
I feel like we might have a good time.

13:15.160 --> 13:16.321
I'm screwing with you.

13:16.560 --> 13:19.689
I was born in London
but I've never been on a private jet.

13:19.880 --> 13:21.484
Ahem, anyway, I clock out at 5:30.

13:21.680 --> 13:25.401
I'll need to stop by the house,
grab a shower, feed the turtle.

13:25.600 --> 13:28.604
I can have a bag packed
and be wheels up by 9.

13:32.880 --> 13:34.450
Sheriff, have you met Kenyon?

13:34.640 --> 13:37.120
He makes a habit of coming into town
for breakfast.

13:37.320 --> 13:40.608
He's a bit of a blowhard
but always friendly, cooperative.

13:40.840 --> 13:44.162
Plus, the church has provided
volunteers for community events...

13:44.360 --> 13:46.010
...search-and-rescue operations.

13:46.200 --> 13:48.441
So, what are you suggesting,
we collar this guy...

13:48.680 --> 13:50.364
...at the next Rotary Club breakfast?

13:50.600 --> 13:53.763
I'm suggesting he can
be talked to. He's reasonable...

13:53.960 --> 13:56.247
...and I'm suggesting
you let my boys handle this...

13:56.480 --> 13:59.563
...instead of lighting this mountain up
and starting World War Ill.

13:59.760 --> 14:02.331
What are the odds
we'll be met with armed resistance?

14:02.520 --> 14:04.124
It's a dead certainty.

14:04.360 --> 14:07.921
You step one foot on Kenyon's land
without his express consent...

14:08.120 --> 14:11.329
...he'll put a bullet in you,
badge or no badge.

14:20.160 --> 14:23.164
We've cleared the estimated kill zone,
evacuated surrounding areas.

14:23.360 --> 14:25.681
We're waiting on a sniper team now.

14:26.280 --> 14:28.886
Hold your fire. It's just...

14:29.440 --> 14:31.408
...a kid.

14:31.640 --> 14:33.608
It's just a kid.

14:37.280 --> 14:38.964
- Excuse me, miss?
- Take this.

14:39.160 --> 14:41.606
Hey, hold on. Hey, halt. No!

14:42.760 --> 14:46.685
Return to the firing line.
Do not approach the suspect.

14:46.880 --> 14:51.169
Return to the firing line.
Do not approach the suspect.

14:57.280 --> 14:59.009
Hi.

15:00.720 --> 15:03.724
I'm Samar. What's your name?

15:07.960 --> 15:09.246
Do you know what that does?

15:11.680 --> 15:14.001
You planned on killing
a lot of people today.

15:15.480 --> 15:16.925
Was that your mission?

15:19.520 --> 15:22.444
It's not going to happen. Do you see?

15:24.800 --> 15:26.484
They're all too far away.

15:27.320 --> 15:31.211
There's no point now.
It's just the two of us out here.

15:31.800 --> 15:36.761
If you push that button,
only two of us are going to die.

15:37.440 --> 15:38.680
Do you understand?

15:38.880 --> 15:43.408
Just you and me,
and I don't want to die today.

15:45.840 --> 15:47.683
Do you?

15:58.360 --> 16:01.523
Come on out. Come on.

16:04.080 --> 16:06.845
Come here, give me your hand.
It's gonna be okay.

